{"id":62043,"title":"Macrophage activation syndrome in Kawasaki disease.","abstract":"Kawasaki disease is an acute febrile vasculitis of childhood. Macrophage activation syndrome is a rare life threatening complication.4-year-old boy with Kawasaki Disease treated with intravenous immunoglobulins.He developed encephalopathy, hepatosplenomegaly and pancytopenia. Blood investigations and bone marrow aspiration suggested macrophage activation syndrome.Good response to pulse methylprednisolone (30 mg/kg/d) for 5 days.Macrophage activation syndrome may complicate Kawasaki disease.","date":"2014-03-17","categories":"Hemic and Lymphatic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24632699","annotations":[{"name":"Pancytopenia","weight":0.894932,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pancytopenia"},{"name":"Macrophage","weight":0.889496,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Macrophage"},{"name":"Methylprednisolone","weight":0.877494,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methylprednisolone"},{"name":"Hepatosplenomegaly","weight":0.824329,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepatosplenomegaly"},{"name":"Vasculitis","weight":0.810695,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vasculitis"},{"name":"Bone marrow examination","weight":0.798641,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bone_marrow_examination"},{"name":"Bone marrow","weight":0.793943,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bone_marrow"},{"name":"Bone","weight":0.75303,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bone"},{"name":"Intravenous therapy","weight":0.734616,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intravenous_therapy"},{"name":"Antibody","weight":0.72365,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antibody"},{"name":"Fever","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fever"},{"name":"Encephalopathy","weight":0.708098,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/En